<DATE>
<P>
April 6, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part 6; Page 2; Column 2; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
86 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: COMING ATTRACTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Writer-newsman Nick Clooney will join his sister, singer Rosemary Clooney, in 
hosting the fourth annual "Singers' Salute to the Songwriter" April 25 at the 
Dorothy Chandler Pavilion. The star-packed musical evening (with Carol Burnett, 
Bob Hope, Dinah Shore and Linda Ronstadt among the performers) is a benefit for 
the Betty Clooney Foundation for Persons With Brain Injury. Nick Clooney, a 
former news anchor at Channel 2 here, now lives in Kentucky and writes a column 
for the Cincinnati Post. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040689-0040 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 40244 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 6, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
