<TEXT>
<P>
Ted R. Capener, vice president for university relations at the University of 
Utah, has been nominated to become the next board chairman of the Public 
Broadcasting Service. If elected at the next board meeting on Wednesday, 
Capener will succeed New York real estate investor-operator and WNET board 
member Alfred R. Stern, who has served four one-year terms as chairman. Capener 
