<P>
Immigration officials refused to free from a Minnesota prison a Dutch visitor 
who says he has AIDS, saying that allowing him to attend a forum on the disease 
might endanger the health of others. "Parole is an extreme item that would be 
used only in extreme circumstances," said Tom Schiltgen, district director of 
the Immigration and Naturalization Service, explaining his rejection of the 
request from Hans Paul Verhoef. However, Schiltgen said a decision is likely 
today on Verhoef's request for a waiver from U.S. immigration laws denying 
entry to persons with a dangerous contagious disease. 
