<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: MALIBU; 
</P>
<P>
BIG ROCK MESA SETTLEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An agreement has been reached among Los Angeles County, Caltrans, 16 Malibu 
homeowners and their insurance companies over a 1983 landslide on Big Rock 
Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
The homeowners, who were not part of a larger settlement involving 238 other 
homeowners, settled for amounts ranging from $200,000 to $250,000, less court 
costs and attorneys' fees. 
</P>
<P>
All but two of the homeowners, who were called the "strays" in the legal battle 
over the landslide, owned properties on the ocean side of Pacific Coast 
Highway, whereas the 238 homeowners who reached a $97-million settlement in 
January live above them on the mountain side. 
</P>
</TEXT>
