WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
CLOTHING LINE ON DISPLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A line of clothing being marketed under the Beverly Hills High School name will 
be shown this month at the Dallas Apparel Market Week, a fashion exposition in 
the Southwest. The clothing line, the subject of a sales and promotional blitz 
nationwide, is being marketed by the Beverly Hills Unified District to raise 
money for teachers and educational programs. Licensing and sales of the BHHS 
line is being handled by 20th-Century Fox. The clothing line is being 
manufactured by Great Southern Co. of Macon, Ga. 
</P>
