<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMPER, WATSON ARE PLAYERS OF YEAR AMONG SOUTH COAST PREPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lakewood High School senior Brian Camper has been named the South Coast boys 
prep basketball Player of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
Camper, who has signed with Arizona State, averaged 20.3 points a game and was 
the most valuable player in the Moore League. 
</P>
<P>
The girls Player of the Year is Lynwood junior Linda Watson. A Parade magazine 
first-team All-American, Watson averaged 22 points, 9.5 rebounds, five assists 
and three steals. She also set a CIF record with 72 three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Odell of Millikan High School was named boys Coach of the Year. Despite 
having only two returning lettermen, Odell led the Rams to the CIF Southern 
Section 5-AA title. He also won his 300th game during the season, his 18th year 
at Millikan. 
</P>
<P>
Margaret Bos of St. Joseph High School in Lakewood is girls Coach of the Year. 
Bos' team was 21-7 this season and went to the 3-A semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
The selections were announced at The Times' annual basketball awards breakfast 
Sunday at the Anaheim Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
In the Southeast area, the Players of the Year are junior Ed O'Bannon of 
Artesia High, who averaged 29 points a game, and sophomore Brenda Pantoja of 
Bell Gardens High, Co-MVP of the Whitmont League. 
</P>
<P>
The top coaches are Bob Brown, who led the Whittier Christian boys team to the 
CIF 2-AA title, and Ken Popkin and Gilberto Limon, co-head coaches at Bell 
Gardens High. Bell Gardens went through the Whitmont League undefeated for the 
second straight season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
