<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMALL BUSINESSES NEED PATRONAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We at Katie McGuire's Pie &amp; Bake Shoppe in Hacienda Heights were one of the 
many small businesses that are taken for granted until we no longer exist. 
</P>
<P>
We tried for almost two years to make a success of Katie McGuire's. The support 
and patronage we received will be a lasting memory. 
</P>
<P>
For customers who came by occasionally or when the nearby Vons grocery store 
was out of something, we only hope our closing serves as a reminder of how 
important it is to support local merchants. It is always easy to visit the big 
department stores, the malls or the discount wholesale clubs. But supporting 
local merchants benefits us all, since such businesses help make the community 
what it is. 
</P>
<P>
Such merchants are not outsiders. They are your neighbors, your friends. Give 
yourself a warm feeling from helping support the "little guy." 
</P>
<P>
Goodby for now. 
</P>
<P>
OLGA and STEVE FELD and the 
</P>
<P>
employees of Katie McGuire's 
</P>
<P>
Hacienda Heights 
</P>
</TEXT>
