<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE POISON CONCERTS CANCELED; SINGER AILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poison's concerts Friday, Saturday and Tuesday in Southern California have been 
canceled. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the band's management company said singer Bret Michaels is 
suffering from bruised vocal cords and is under doctor's orders not to sing or 
speak. 
</P>
<P>
Canceled were shows set for the Los Angeles Sports Arena, the Pacific 
Amphitheatre and the San Diego Sports Arena. No decision has been made about 
rescheduling the shows. Ticket refunds are available at the point of purchase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040689-0162 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 40552 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 6, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
