<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
IRAN HANGS 66 MORE DRUG DEALERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran hanged 66 drug dealers today, raising the total number of traffickers who 
have been executed to 379 since a major drive to stamp out the narcotics trade 
was launched in January. 
</P>
<P>
Today's executions took place in Tehran, where 17 were hanged, and 19 other 
cities around the country, the official news agency IRNA reported. Tehran 
radio, monitored in Cyprus, quoted Prosecutor General Moussavi Khoeini as 
saying, "The executions will continue as long as even a single dealer is left 
in the country." 
</P>
</TEXT>
